The patch should be applied to Revision7072 from svn://tron.homeunix.org/ja2/trunk
Should for some reason this SVN come offline, you can try dropping me a mail at
(omnigraphical @ gmail . com) but I can't promise I'll answer.
Questions regarding installation/patching/playing/whatever should be asked in
the Ja2Galaxy Forum or anddev.org.

Building is a little complicated:

ATTENTION: i forgot to deactivate the drop_all mod in the patch, please change droprates
back to normal if you want 100%pure Stracciatella feeling!


- Create an android build environment on you machine - google will help you with that.
(as the time of writing the NDKr6 is the most recent available NDK)
- You should use Crystax Toolchain instead. I used CrystaX-r6-2.

- Obtain the freshest pelyaSDL from github here https://github.com/pelya/commandergenius
I used version up to commit 8e16ec9f333ca3bbe11b15e1d2e0ae9e9d4b64be
(Beware: pelya breaks the whole thing sometimes...)

- follow pelyas instructions on how to compile your own application
  -  for sources you should of course use the checked out SVN of JA2 Stracciatella
     patched with the supplied patch.
     (run 'patch -p1 -i ja2_strac_svnr7072_to_ja2android_rc2.patch')
NOTE: I have not tested patching it with the new patch - but it should work. (you only need this patch!)
  - copy over the Icon and the two build and config files

- run build.sh from the pelya trunk, grab your phone and play some Exult while JA2 is
  building.

- you should now have a .apk file you can install on your phone

- Don't forget to move over your JA2 Data folder before trying to run the game.
  YES, OF COURSE YOU NEED TO OWN THE ORIGINAL GAME - it should be still in the stores!

- Hopefully: have fun!


~omnigraphical

